EXAMPLE:

### Features

- Add new feature ([`abcdef0`](https://domain.com/namespace/repo/commit/HASH))
- **scope**: Add new feature ([`abcdef1`](https://domain.com/namespace/repo/commit/HASH))

### Bug Fixes

- Fix bug ([`abcdef2`](https://domain.com/namespace/repo/commit/HASH))

NOTE: this template is a slimmed-down override of the default conventional/md
`changes.md.j2`. It deliberately drops:
  - the "Breaking Changes" body-rendering section
  - the "Additional Release Information" release-notice section
  - any commit body content (Co-Authored-By, Refs #N, phase narrative)

Only the subject line + scope + hash link is rendered. Filtering by commit
type (feat/fix/perf only) is configured via
`[tool.semantic_release.changelog].exclude_commit_patterns` in pyproject.toml.

